Apparently, this is simply a rhythmic game that requires you to smash your button rapidly and yet precisely but in it essence, it's a charming delight! Only pushing your left mouse button and right one streamlines the control scheme down to the basics, but the skill involved is quite the attraction. You fight enemies in different colours and they should be fought in diffrent combos of these two mouse buttons. Some bosses even change their colours in the middle, giving you quite a challenge and requiring your reflexes to be paced up as much as possible. There are also various cute art designs here and there, including the destroyable objects, which even play a role in some levels that require you to smash a certain amount of objects to win. As enemies with new colours and new gameplay mechanisms emerge every some levels, it rarely gets boring. I'd say this is a masterpiece with creativity wrapped in a relatively low budget look. You wouldn't regret it once you tried!
